name: Ashton Jeanty
summary: Boise State's Ashton Jeanty, a leading contender for the Heisman Trophy and college football's rushing record, has announced his intention to enter the NFL Draft after the 2023 season. The news comes after a stellar year in which he helped lead the Broncos to the Mountain West title and is considered one of the most impactful players in the 2024 draft class. Jeanty's decision follows support from legendary running back Barry Sanders, who holds the NCAA rushing record. Jeanty's departure will mark the end of his impressive Boise State career, where he has left an enduring mark on the program's history.

summary: Mark Withers, a renowned actor known for his roles in the television series "Dynasty" and "Stranger Things," has passed away at the age of 77. The cause of his death was a battle with pancreatic cancer. Withers portrayed the character of Jason Colby in the original "Dynasty" series, which aired from 1981 to 1989. He also appeared in the 2017 Netflix series "Stranger Things" as Officer James Hopper's father, Lonnie. His death has been met with tributes and condolences from colleagues and fans alike, who remember him for his warmth, humor, and dedication to his craft.
